<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/315</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Eastern
                                European Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KRF1"><hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi></persName>)<note n="20" xml:id="d206fn20">Addressed
                                to the Secretary of State, the Under Secretary of State, Assistant
                                Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_MRW1">Moore</persName>, and
                                Assistant Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_SFB1">Sayre</persName>.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-06">April 6, 1935</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>If Mr. <persName>Litvinoff</persName> confirms in writing that Soviet
                            purchases in the United States in 1935 will probably amount to some
                            $30,000,000, I think that we should consider that such assurance is
                            quite adequate and furnishes a satisfactory basis for generalizing to
                            the Soviet Union tariff concessions accorded other countries.</p>
                        <p>You will note from the following figures that purchases in the amount of
                            $30,000,000 will involve a considerable increase over Soviet purchases
                            in the United States in recent years:</p>
                        <p rend="center">
                            <hi rend="italic">American Exports to the Soviet Union</hi>
                        </p>
                        <table cols="3" rend="width: 50%" rendition="#center-block" rows="3">
                            <row>
                                <cell>1932</cell>
                                <cell>—</cell>
                                <cell role="num">$12,640,891</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>1933</cell>
                                <cell>—</cell>
                                <cell role="num">8,997,307</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>1934</cell>
                                <cell>—</cell>
                                <cell role="num">14,866,515</cell>
                            </row>
                        </table>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_KRF1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert</hi> F. <hi rend="smallcaps">Kelley</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>